ing mastery of mountain environments through technology and speed—two central features distinguishing early twentieth-century cultures.Skiing into Modernity surpasses existing literature on the history of skiing to explore intersections between work, tourism, leisure, development, environmental destruction, urbanism, and more.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSkis and skiingxSocial aspectszAlps. 0aSkis and skiingzAlpsxHistory. 0aTourismzAlpsxHistory. 70(DE-601)1060796970(DE-588)4077587-2aSozialer Wandel2gnd 70(DE-601)1061350230(DE-588)4061616-2aUmwelt2gnd 70(DE-601)1061590540(DE-588)4055245-7aSkisport2gnd 70(DE-601)1062532200(DE-588)4034348-0aLandschaftsentwicklung2gnd 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Skiing.2bisacsh  a20th century sports history.  aalpine skiers.  acentral europe.  acompetition.  acultural studies.  adevelopment.  aenvironmental destruction.  aenvironmental studies.  aeurope.  aeuropean history.  ahistorical.  aleisure practices.  aleisure.  amodern alps.  amountain environments.  amountains.  anature.  aretrospective.  ascandinavian.  askiing across the world.  askiing.  askis.  asnow skiing.  aspeed.  asport in world history series.  asports history.  asports.  atechnology.  atourism.  aurbanism.  awilderness.  awork.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028427240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095989740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959897/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY